---
const steps = [
  {
    num: "01",
    title: "Verify support",
    body: "The agent should confirm whether the project is Next.js, Astro, or React/Vite. If not, it should stop instead of forcing a broken integration.",
  },
  {
    num: "02",
    title: "Inspect the repo",
    body: "Have the agent read package.json, config files, and app structure before touching anything. It should name the platform and explain why.",
  },
  {
    num: "03",
    title: "Install the right adapter",
    body: "Use the official Yamblog package pair for the detected platform and follow local project conventions for package manager and file layout.",
  },
  {
    num: "04",
    title: "Create a sample post",
    body: "A first hello-world.md file proves the content path, frontmatter parsing, and route wiring are all correct.",
  },
  {
    num: "05",
    title: "Self-heal and verify",
    body: "If imports, routes, or paths fail, the agent should repair the integration and re-check instead of stopping at the first error.",
  },
];

const promptLines = [
  "You are integrating Yamblog (https://github.com/yamblog/yamblog).",
  "Inspect first, then implement. Never invent API names, and never",
  "claim success without running the verification step.",
  "",
  "1. Detect the platform from package.json and config files:",
  "   Next.js    → @yamblog/core + @yamblog/next",
  "   Astro      → @yamblog/core + @yamblog/astro",
  "   React/Vite → @yamblog/core (+ @yamblog/react for UI)",
  "   Anything else: stop and propose a safe fallback with core only.",
  "2. Install with the project's own package manager.",
  "3. Create the content dir (content/posts, or src/content/posts on",
  "   Astro) and a shared instance:",
  "   export const blog = defineBlog('<content dir>');",
  "4. Create hello-world.md — today's date, no slug field:",
  "   ---",
  '   title: "Hello World"',
  '   date: "<YYYY-MM-DD>"',
  '   author: "Your Name"',
  '   tags: ["intro"]',
  '   excerpt: "My first post powered by Yamblog."',
  "   draft: false",
  "   ---",
  "",
  "   Welcome to my blog, powered by **Yamblog**.",
  "5. Wire a listing page (blog.getPosts()) and a post page",
  "   (blog.getPostBySlug(slug)) using documented adapter exports.",
  "6. Verify: blog.validateContent() passes, getPostBySlug('hello-world')",
  "   returns the post, and the blog route renders. Fix and re-verify on",
  "   any failure, then report what you did.",
];
---

<section id="agents" class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div>
        <div class="section-eyebrow">For agents</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">
          Give your coding agent one prompt. Let it <em>inspect, verify,</em> and
          integrate.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <p class="section-lead">
        The prompt tells the model to detect the platform, confirm Yamblog
        support, install the right adapter, create a sample post, and
        self-correct if the first pass is wrong.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="agent">
      <!-- Steps -->
      <div class="agent-steps">
        {
          steps.map((step) => (
            <div class="agent-step">
              <div class="num">{step.num}</div>
              <div>
                <h4>{step.title}</h4>
                <p>{step.body}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </div>

      <!-- Setup prompt (sticky) -->
      <div class="code-shell" style="position: sticky; top: 84px;">
        <div class="code-tabs">
          <div class="code-tab active">
            <span class="dot"></span>prompt-for-llms.md
          </div>
          <button
            class="code-copy"
            data-copy={promptLines.join('\n')}
            data-label="Copy"
          >
            <svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="9" y="9" width="13" height="13" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M5 15H4a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h9a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v1"/></svg>
            Copy
          </button>
        </div>
        <div class="code-body">
          {
            promptLines.map((ln, i) => (
              <div class="code-line">
                <span class="ln">{i + 1}</span>
                <span
                  class={
                    ln.startsWith("#")
                      ? "tk-c"
                      : ln.match(/^\d\./)
                        ? "tk-k"
                        : ""
                  }
                >
                  {ln}
                </span>
              </div>
            ))
          }
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top: 24px; color: var(--c-muted);">
      Need the full version? Read <a href="/prompt-for-llms/">Prompt for LLMs</a
      >.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
